## 15.17 A worked example

You have two implementations of `sum-of-squares`. Which is faster?

```scheme
(define (sum-of-squares-1 xs)
  (apply + (map (lambda (x) (* x x)) xs)))

(define (sum-of-squares-2 xs)
  (fold + 0 (map (lambda (x) (* x x)) xs)))

(define big (range 10000))

(let ((t0 (current-time-ms)))
  (sum-of-squares-1 big)
  (display (- (current-time-ms) t0)))

(let ((t0 (current-time-ms)))
  (sum-of-squares-2 big)
  (display (- (current-time-ms) t0)))
```

Run both. Compare wall times. Winner wins.

You can do the same for fuel and memory. Three axes, three measurements. Pick the implementation that wins the axis you care about.

